<title type="html"><![CDATA[MMC1 &amp; VRC1 -- 74 series style]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1866&amp;p=15978#p15978"><![CDATA[
It's only been tested in real time simulation (which should be good enough) for this sort of design.This was just to give people a tease, the logic needs to be verified, simplified and more tightly integratated if this is to be built. This certainly wouldn't be a fun thing to build, way too many wires.<br /><br />I have conflicting information (Kevtris vs Martin Korth) on the hor/ver mirroring bits which needs to be addressed. Also I can't seem to find info on which bank is static at $8000 in $c000 swappable mode. So those are two big issues which need to be resolved. If you include my edits in my first post, I think all the logic is there (well, maybe not :P)<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=20">kyuusaku</a> — Fri Aug 04, 2006 12:31 pm</p><hr />
